cholarship</span><span> as a reward</span><span>.</span> \n	</p>\n</div>\n<br />'),
(148, '星展银行董事长何潮辉先生精彩开讲', 'cn', 0, 6, '', '', '<p style="text-indent:24pt;">\n	<span style="font-size:12px;font-family:宋体;">2012</span><span style="font-size:12pt;font-family:宋体;"><span style="font-size:12px;">年</span><span style="font-size:12px;">10</span><span style="font-size:12px;">月</span><span style="font-size:12px;">25</span><span style="font-size:12px;">日，星展银行（中国）有限公司董事长何潮辉先生作为演讲嘉宾，为同学们带来了一场关于“全球经济与银行业的近期发展如何启示及影响中国银行业发展”的主题演讲。我院陆雄文院长出席了本次活动，财务金融系孙谦教授主持了讲座。　</span></span> \n</p>\n<p style="text-indent:24pt;" align="center">\n	<span style="font-size:12pt;font-family:宋体;"><span style="font-size:12px;"></span><img alt="" src="http://msc.fdsm.fudan.edu.cn/uploads/image/20121026/20121026172903_56488.jpg" height="225" width="300" /><span></span></span> \n</p>\n<p style="text-indent:24pt;">\n	<span style="font-size:12pt;font-family:宋体;"><span style="font-size:12px;">讲座伊始，何潮辉先生简要介绍了其个人履历，从</span><span style="font-size:12px;">1994</span><span style="font-size:12px;">年作为毕马威中国的首席代表回国工作，全力开展毕马威在中国的业务，到</span><span style="font-size:12px;">08</span><span style="font-size:12px;">年创立厚朴投资管理公司，再到如今就任星展银行（中国）有限公司董事长，何潮辉先生在财务金融行业的卓越成就，使在场同学歆羡不已。</span><span></span></span> \n</p>\n<p style="text-indent:24pt;">\n	<span style="font-size:12pt;font-family:宋体;"><span style="font-size:12px;">随后，何潮辉先生从当前全球经济形势谈起，通过图表为大家展示了美国实施量化宽松政策后，其面临急剧自动增税和支出削减的“财政悬崖”，并详细阐述了政府政策与次贷危机的潜在关系。政府主导金融机构的分与合以及住房所有权目标，加之银行业的过度杠杆化，导致了金融危机的发生。同时，政府过度杠杆化则导致了意大利、德国等欧洲国家的主权债务危机。</span></span> \n</p>\n<p style="text-indent:24pt;" align="center">\n	<span style="font-size:12pt;font-family:宋体;"><img alt="" src="http://msc.fdsm.fudan.edu.cn/uploads/image/20121026/20121026172930_81872.jpg" height="225" width="300" /><span style="font-size:12px;"></span></span> \n</p>\n<p style="text-indent:24pt;">\n	<span style="font-size:12pt;font-family:宋体;"><span style="font-size:12px;">在此基础上，何潮辉先生指出，从金融危机中，我们应当认识到五个关键问题，即：大而不能倒、政治目标凌驾于业务决策、过度杠杆信贷、不当销售和风险意识不足。之后，何潮辉先生对照中国现状，就上述问题进行了一一阐述，并就中国银行业是否存在破产可能与在座同学进行了热烈的讨论。</span><span></span></span> \n</p>\n<p style="text-indent:24pt;">\n	<span style="font-size:12pt;font-family:宋体;"><span style="font-size:12px;">在聆听了何潮辉先生的精彩演讲后，结合其在金融业界丰富的经历，现场同学纷纷提出了各自关心的问题。问题涵盖了宏观经济层面“在量化宽松政策下，中国为何仍持有美国大量债务”，银行监管层面“如何防范理财产品不当销售”，以及微观层面“星展银行如何面临潜在挑战”等多个问题。何潮辉先生敏锐的洞悉力和独到的见解，让在座同学受益匪浅。整场讲座在热烈的掌声中圆满结束。</span><span></span></span> \n</p>', '', '', '', '', '/201210/26/103354e5gbomoernmr42e4.jpg', '2012年10月25日，星展银行（中国）有限公司董事长何潮辉先生作为演讲嘉宾，为同学们带来了一场关于“全球经济与银行业的近期发展如何启示及影响中国银行业发展”的主题演讲。我院陆雄文院长出席了本次活动，财务金融系孙谦教授主持了讲座。', 1351218843, 0, 1, '', 6, 'November 1, 2012', 'Wonderful Speech delivered by Mr. Ho Dominic Chiu Fai, President of DBS', 'In October 25, 2012, DBS Bank (China) Co., Ltd. Chairman Mr. He Chaohui as the guest speaker, for students to bring On October 25, 2012, as a guest speaker, Mr. Ho Dominic Chiu Fai, President of DBS Bank (China) Co., Ltd. delivered to students a keynote speech on “How Does the Recent Development of World Economy and Global Banking Industry Enlighten the Development of China Banking Industry”. Lu Xiongwen, Dean of School of Management, Fudan University (FDSM), attended this event, and Professor S', '<p style="text-indent:24pt;">\n	<span style="font-size:12px;font-family:宋体;"> </span> \n</p>\n<div id="trans-result-content" lang="EN-US">\n	<p>\n		<span class="">\n		<p style="margin-left:0cm;text-indent:24.0pt;background:white;">\n			<span style="font-size:9.0pt;font-family:&quot;color:#3B3B3B;">On October 25, 2012, as a guest speaker, Mr. Ho Dominic Chiu\nFai, President of DBS Bank (China) Co., Ltd. delivered to students a keynote\nspeech on “How Does the Recent Development of World Economy and Global Banking\nIndustry Enlighten the Development of China Banking Industry”. Lu Xiongwen,\nDean of School of Management, Fudan University (FDSM), attended this event, and\nProfessor Sun Qian of Department of Finance chaired this lecture.</span><span style="font-size:9.0pt;font-family:&quot;color:#3B3B3B;"></span>\n		</p>\n</span><span class=""></span> \n	</p>\n</div>\n<span style="font-size:12pt;font-family:宋体;"><span style="font-size:12px;"></span><span style="font-size:12px;"></span><span style="font-size:12px;"></span><span style="font-size:12px;"></span><span style="font-size:12px;"></span></span> \n<p>\n	<br />\n</p>\n<p style="text-indent:24pt;" align="center">\n	<span style="font-size:12pt;font-family:宋体;"><span style="font-size:12px;"></span><img alt="" src="http://msc.fdsm.fudan.edu.cn/uploads/image/20121026/20121026172903_56488.jpg" height="225" width="300" /><span></span></span> \n</p>\n<p style="text-indent:24pt;">\n	<span style="font-size:12pt;font-family:宋体;"><span style="font-size:12px;"> </span></span> \n</p>\n<div id="trans-result-content" lang="EN-US">\n	<p>\n		<span class="">\n		<p style="margin-left:0cm;text-indent:24.0pt;background:white;">\n			<span style="font-size:9.0pt;font-family:&quot;color:#3B3B3B;">At the very beginning of this lecture, Mr. Ho Dominic Chiu Fai\nbriefly introduced himself: in 1994, he as the chief representative of KPMG\nreturned home to work and spared no pains to develop the business of KPMG in\nChina; in 2008, he founded Hopu Investment Management Co; now, he is acting as\nPresident of DBS Bank (China) Co., Ltd. Mr. Ho’s outstanding achievements in\nthe finance industry became the envy of the present students.</span>\n		</p>\n		<p style="margin-left:0cm;text-indent:24.0pt;background:white;">\n			<p style="margin-left:0cm;text-indent:24.0pt;background:white;">\n				<span style="font-size:9.0pt;font-family:&quot;color:#3B3B3B;">hen, starting from the current world economy, Mr. Ho used some\ncharts to show the audiences that US has been confronted with the “financial\ncliff” represented by sharp, automatic tax increases and spending cuts after\nimplementing the quantitative easing policy, and detailed the potential\nrelationship between the government policy and the subprime crisis. According\nto Mr. Ho, such separation and combination of financial institutions as led by\nthe government and the housing ownership objective, along with excessive\nleverage of the banking industry, resulted into the financial crisis;\nmeanwhile, the excessive leverage by the government also led to the sovereign\ndebt crisis in European countries such as Italy and Germany.</span><span style="font-size:9.0pt;font-family:&quot;color:#3B3B3B;"></span>\n			</p>\n<br />\n<span style="font-size:9.0pt;font-family:&quot;color:#3B3B3B;"></span><span style="font-size:9.0pt;font-family:&quot;color:#3B3B3B;"></span>\n		</p>\n</span>\n	</p>\n	<p>\n		<span></span><span></span><span class=""></span><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span><span class=""></span><span></span><span></span><span class=""></span><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span><span class=""></span><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span><span class=""></span><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span><span class=""></span><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span><span class=""></span><span class=""></span><span></span><span class=""></span><span class=""></span><span class=""></span> \n	</p>\n</div>\n<p>\n	<br />\n</p>\n<p style="text-indent:24pt;">\n	<span style="font-size:12pt;font-family:宋体;"><span style="font-size:12px;"></span></span> \n</p>\n<p style="text-indent:24pt;" align="center">\n	<span style="font-size:12pt;font-family:宋体;"><img alt="" src="http://msc.fdsm.fudan.edu.cn/uploads/image/20121026/20121026172930_81872.jpg" height="225" width="300" /><span style="font-size:12px;"></span></span> \n</p>\n<p style="text-indent:24pt;">\n	<span style="font-size:12pt;font-family:宋体;"><span style="font-size:12px;"> </span></span> \n</p>\n<div id="trans-result-content" lang="EN-US">\n	<p>\n		<span class="">\n		<p style="margin-left:0cm;text-align:left;text-indent:24.0pt;background:white;" align="left">\n			<span style="font-size:9.0pt;font-family:&quot;color:#3B3B3B;">On this basis, Mr. Ho pointed out that from this financial\ncrisis five key problems should be understood, namely, too big to fail,\nbusiness decisions outmatched by the political objective, excessive leverage of\ncredit, wrongful sales, and lack of risk awareness. After that, Ho presented\nthe above problems one by one in line with the status quo of China, and carried\nout a heated discussion with the present students about whether China banking\nindustry may go bankrupt or not.</span>\n		</p>\n		<p style="margin-left:0cm;text-align:left;text-indent:24.0pt;background:white;" align="left">\n			<p style="margin-left:0cm;text-indent:24.0pt;background:white;">\n				<span style="font-size:9.0pt;font-family:&quot;color:#3B3B3B;">After hearing this spectacular speech by Mr. Ho Dominic Chiu\nFai, the present students raised questions of concern according to Ho’s rich\nexperiences in the finance industry. These questions involved “why is China\nstill holding a large number of liabilities of US under the quantitative easing\npolicy” from a macro-economic perspective, “how should the banking regulators\nprevent the wrongful sales of financial products” and “how should SDB meet\npotential challenges”. Mr. Ho’s keen insights and original views benefited the\nstudents on the scene. Finally, this lecture successfully ended amid warm\napplause.</span><span style="font-size:9.0pt;font-family:&quot;color:#3B3B3B;"></span>\n			</p>\n<br />\n<span style="font-size:9.0pt;font-family:&quot;color:#3B3B3B;"></span><span style="font-size:9.0pt;font-family:&quot;color:#3B3B3B;"></span>\n		</p>\n</span>\n	</p>\n</div>\n<p>\n	<br />\n</p>\n<p style="text-indent:24pt;">\n	<span style="font-size:12pt;font-family:宋体;"><span style="font-size:12px;"></span><span></span></span> \n</p>\n　 <br />\n<br />\n<br />'),
(122, 'Paolo Epifani', 'cn', 0, 31, '', '', '<p>\n	<br />\n</p>\n<p>\n	<object id="ieooui" classid="clsid:38481807-CA0E-42D2-BF39-B33AF135CC4D">\n	</object>\n<style>\nst1:*{behavior:url(#ieooui) }\n</style>\n</p>\n<p style="vertical-align:top;">\n	<a href="http://ddim.seabig.cn/uploads/201210/16/153735xiaua69xbu3fs7dy.jpg" target="_blank"></a> \n</p>\n<p style="text-align:center;">\n	<img alt="" src="http://ddim.seabig.cn/uploads/201210/16/153735xiaua69xbu3fs7dy.jpg.thumb.jpg" height="300" width="209" /> \n</p>\n<p style="vertical-align:top;">\n	<span style="FONT-FAMILY: " mso-ansi-language:="" black;="" color:="" mso-bidi-font-family:="" calibri?,?sans-serif?;="" ?times="" new="" roman?;="" en-gb;?="" lang="EN-GB">Paolo Epifani is Associate Professor of Economics at Bocconi University Milan, and Research fellow at IGIER Milan. He teaches International Economics at Bocconi University and at Fudan University Shanghai. He does research on international trade and the economic consequences of globalization. His works are published in leading economics journals, such as <em style="mso-bidi-font-style:normal;">The Review of Economic Studies</em>, <em style="mso-bidi-font-style:normal;">The Review of Economics and Statistics, The Economic Journal,</em> <em style="mso-bidi-font-style:normal;">The Journal of International Economics</em>.</span> \n</p>\n<p>\n	<br />\n</p>', '', '', '', '', '/201210/18/153211ko0nybrhpa9vzksy.jpg', 'Paolo Epifani is Associate Professor of Economics at Bocconi University Milan, and Research fellow at IGIER Milan. He teaches International Economics at Bocconi University and at Fudan University Shan', 1350373100, 0, 1, '', 0, '', 'Paolo Epifani', 'Paolo Epifani is Associate Professor of Economics at Bocconi University Milan, and Research fellow at IGIER Milan. He teaches International Economics at Bocconi University and at Fudan University Shan', '<p>\n	<br />\n</p>\n<p>\n	<br />\n</p>\n<p style="vertical-align:top;">\n	<br />\n</p>\n<p style="tex