(137, 'Zhao Youzhen 赵优珍', 'cn', 0, 31, '', '', '<p style="text-align:center;">\r\n	<strong><a href="http://ddim.seabig.cn/uploads/201210/18/104603ln25eoxtbsq7qgl2.jpg" target="_blank"><img style="border-right:0px;border-top:0px;border-left:0px;border-bottom:0px;" alt="" src="http://ddim.seabig.cn/uploads/201210/18/104603ln25eoxtbsq7qgl2.jpg.thumb.jpg" width="500" /></a></strong> \r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<strong>Dr. Youzhen (Jane) ZHAO</strong> is Associate Professor of International Business and Strategy at School of Management, Fudan University. She has got Bachelor in Science, Master in Economics and PhD in Management from Fudan University, China.\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	She was a visiting professor at Bocconi University (2010), MIT (2005), University of Oregon (2004) and Washington University in St. Louis (2000). Dr. Zhao participated in the PCMPCL (Program on Case Method and Participant-Centered Learning) at Harvard Business School in 2008 and at Nanyang Technological University in 2009. She also visited LUISS, Italy (2010 &amp; 2012), Payap University, Thailand (2012), Yeungnam University, South Korea (2010), Norwegian Business School (2006, 2007, 2008, 2009 &amp; 2010), FDC, Brazil (2009), Columbia University (2007 &amp; 2008), Danjiang University, Taiwan (2008), University of Pennsylvania(2007), Appalachian State University (2007), Aoyama Gakuin University, Japan (2006) and University of Hong Kong(2005) for short-term academic exchange. Her recent research interests include Cross-border M&amp;As of Chinese firms, International New Ventures from China, Outward FDI promotion system, Regional Headquarters and R&amp;D centers of MNEs in China. She is the principal investigator of research projects from National Natural Science Foundation of China, Ministry of Education of China, the Foundation for Shanghai Philosophy and Social Sciences Program, Innovation Program of Shanghai Municipal Education Commission, Shanghai Municipal Commission of Commerce, Fudan University, Bao Steel &nbsp;as well as international organizations such as Norwegian Research Council and The Fondazione Cariplo. She has been awarded honors such as "First Prize in Teaching Achievements of Fudan University", "Model Course Taught in English" by Shanghai Education Commission, "Outstanding Teaching Award", "Kodak Award for Teaching Excellence", "First Prize Teaching Award", "Star of the Century", "Best advisor to undergraduates" by Fudan University in recent years.\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;Dr. ZHAO is member of Academy of Management, Academy of International Business, China International Association of Management Research, and the Chinese Institute of Certified Public Accountants.\r\n</p>', '', '', '', '', '/201210/18/104718wuavcdrzurbsv5si.jpg', 'Dr. Youzhen (Jane) ZHAO is Associate Professor of International Business and Strategy at School of Management, Fudan University. She has got Bachelor in Science, Master in Economics and PhD in Managem', 1350528485, 0, 1, '', 0, '', 'Zhao Youzhen ', 'Dr. Youzhen (Jane) ZHAO is Associate Professor of International Business and Strategy at School of Management, Fudan University. She has got Bachelor in Science, Master in Economics and PhD in Managem', '<p style="text-align:center;">\r\n	<strong><a href="http://ddim.seabig.cn/uploads/201210/18/104603ln25eoxtbsq7qgl2.jpg" target="_blank"><img style="border-right:0px;border-top:0px;border-left:0px;border-bottom:0px;" alt="" src="http://ddim.seabig.cn/uploads/201210/18/104603ln25eoxtbsq7qgl2.jpg.thumb.jpg" width="500" /></a></strong> \r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<strong>Dr. Youzhen (Jane) ZHAO</strong> is Associate Professor of International Business and Strategy at School of Management, Fudan University. She has got Bachelor in Science, Master in Economics and PhD in Management from Fudan University, China.\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	She was a visiting professor at Bocconi University (2010), MIT (2005), University of Oregon (2004) and Washington University in St. Louis (2000). Dr. Zhao participated in the PCMPCL (Program on Case Method and Participant-Centered Learning) at Harvard Business School in 2008 and at Nanyang Technological University in 2009. She also visited LUISS, Italy (2010 &amp; 2012), Payap University, Thailand (2012), Yeungnam University, South Korea (2010), Norwegian Business School (2006, 2007, 2008, 2009 &amp; 2010), FDC, Brazil (2009), Columbia University (2007 &amp; 2008), Danjiang University, Taiwan (2008), University of Pennsylvania(2007), Appalachian State University (2007), Aoyama Gakuin University, Japan (2006) and University of Hong Kong(2005) for short-term academic exchange. Her recent research interests include Cross-border M&amp;As of Chinese firms, International New Ventures from China, Outward FDI promotion system, Regional Headquarters and R&amp;D centers of MNEs in China. She is the principal investigator of research projects from National Natural Science Foundation of China, Ministry of Education of China, the Foundation for Shanghai Philosophy and Social Sciences Program, Innovation Program of Shanghai Municipal Education Commission, Shanghai Municipal Commission of Commerce, Fudan University, Bao Steel &nbsp;as well as international organizations such as Norwegian Research Council and The Fondazione Cariplo. She has been awarded honors such as "First Prize in Teaching Achievements of Fudan University", "Model Course Taught in English" by Shanghai Education Commission, "Outstanding Teaching Award", "Kodak Award for Teaching Excellence", "First Prize Teaching Award", "Star of the Century", "Best advisor to undergraduates" by Fudan University in recent years.\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;Dr. ZHAO is member of Academy of Management, Academy of International Business, China International Association of Management Research, and the Chinese Institute of Certified Public Accountants.\r\n</p>\r\n<br />');
