(140, 'Raffaella Piccarreta', 'cn', 0, 31, '', '', '<p align="center">\n	<img alt="" src="/uploads/image/20121018/20121018163124_17904.bmp" /> \n</p>\n<p>\n	<br />\n</p>\n<p>\n	<strong>Biographical note</strong> \n</p>\n<div>\n	<p>\n		Degree in Economics and Social Sciences from Università Bocconi. PhD in Statistics from the Università di Trento.\n	</p>\n</div>\n<h2>\n	<br />\nAcademic CV\n</h2>\n<div>\n	<p>\n		Researcher in Statistics. At Università Bocconi she has taught Statistics, Computing, Applied Economics, Economic Statistics, Sample Surveys, Statistics for Ecoomics and Business (EMIT, LS), Data Analysis (PhD in Business Administration and Management, PhD in Statistics). She taught Statistics and economic statistics at the Faculty of Economics, Università dell’Insubria, and Statistics at the Faculty of Political Science, Università Cattolica del Sacro Cuore. <br />\nShe visited CSSS (Center for Statistics and the Social Science), University of Washington, Seattle, USA, from September 2008 to December 2008, and the Dept. of Social Science Research Methods, Faculty of Social Sciences, Vrije Universiteit Amsterdam from September 2007 to December 2007.<br />\n<br />\nShe was&nbsp;a referee for the following&nbsp;journals: Journal of Applied Statistics; Sociological Methods and Research; Statistics in Medicine; Statistical Methods and Applications; Advances in Life Course Research.\n	</p>\n	<p>\n		She is a member of the Società Italiana di Statistica (SIS). She is fellow of ‘Carlo F. Dondena‘ Centre for Research on Social Dynamics. <br />\nShe obtained the award Indennità di eccellenza nella ricerca, Bocconi University (academic years 2008 and 2009).\n	</p>\n</div>\n<h2>\n	<br />\nResearch areas\n</h2>\n<div>\n	<p>\n		Multivariate (and complex) data analysis. Categorical data analysis. Sequence Analysis. Classification and Regression trees (for ordinal response variables). Analysis of Dissimilarity matrices. Genetic algorithms. Neural networks.\n	</p>\n</div>\n<h2>\n	<br />\nSelected publications\n</h2>\n<div>\n	<p>\n		<span style="font-weight:bold;"><br />\nRefereed journals papers</span>: Binary trees for dissimilarity data, forthcoming <span style="font-weight:bold;">2010</span>, <span style="font-style:italic;">Computational Statistics and Data Analysis</span>; Exploring sequences: A graphical tool based upon Multidimensional Scaling (joint withOrna Lior), JRSS Series A, <span style="font-weight:bold;">2010</span>, 173, pp. 165-184; Strings of Adulthood: A Sequence Analysis of Young Women’s Work-family Trajectories (joint with Arnstein Aassve and Francesco Billari), <span style="font-style:italic;">European Journal of Population</span>, <span style="font-weight:bold;">2007</span>, vol. 23, pp. 369-388; Clustering Work and Family Trajectories using a Divisive Algorithm, (joint with Francesco Billari), <span style="font-style:italic;">JRSS Series A</span>, <span style="font-weight:bold;">2007</span>, 170, pp. 1061-1078; Classification Trees for Ordinal Variables, <span style="font-style:italic;">Computational Statistics</span>, <span style="font-weight:bold;">2008</span>, 23, pp. 407-427; Analysing Demographic Life Courses through Sequence Analysis, (joint with Francesco Billari), <span style="font-style:italic;">Mathematical Population Studies</span>, 12, <span style="font-weight:bold;">2005</span>, pp. 1-27; Sequence Analysis of BHPS Life Courses Data, (joint with Arnstein Aassve and Francesco Billari) in <span style="font-style:italic;">New Developments in Classification and Data Analysis</span>, M. Vichi, P. Monari, S. Mignani, A. Montanari, eds., pp. 275-284, Springer-Verlag, Heidelberg <span style="font-weight:bold;">2004</span>; Ordinal classification trees based on impurity measures, in <span style="font-style:italic;">Advances in Multivariate Data Analysis</span>, Bock-Chiodi-Mineo, eds., pp. 39-51, Springer-Verlag, Heidelberg <span style="font-weight:bold;">2004</span>; A New Measure of Nominal-OrdinalAssociatio